            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>sweet pointed pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and finely dice</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your<strong> tomato paste</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) in 400ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [600ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1713869528152-x200.jpg",
